[{"id":"VH980572","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram. In the diagram, land is shown on the left, and a lake is shown on the right. In the top portion of the land, a dot is shown near the edge of the lake. Directly below this dot is another dot at the edge of the lake. The vertical distance between the two dots is labeled x. In the bottom portion of the lake, an island is shown. The horizontal distance from the island to the edge of the lake is 1 mile. The vertical distance from the island to the dot in the top portion of land is 4 miles.\" height=\"251\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH980572.g04.png\" width=\"230\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An athlete is planning for the “Land and Lake Race,” the path of which is shown in the figure above. The contestants will start at the dot, run up to 4&nbsp;miles along the beach, enter the water at any time, and swim to the island. The athlete estimates that they can run along the beach at a constant rate of 8&nbsp;miles&nbsp;per&nbsp;hour and swim at a constant rate of 2&nbsp;miles&nbsp;per&nbsp;hour. Let <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"T\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></math></span></span> be a function that represents the time to complete the race, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is the distance in miles that the athlete runs and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T of x\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"T of x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>T</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is measured in hours. Which of the following methods best explains how to determine the minimum time, in hours, the athlete should run along the beach and then swim to the island?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH980572_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Let <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T of x, equal, 8 x, plus 2 times the square root of 1 squared, plus, open parenthesis, 4 minus x, close parenthesis, squared, end root\"><math alttext=\"T of x, equal, 8 x, plus 2 times the square root of 1 squared, plus, open parenthesis, 4 minus x, close parenthesis, squared, end root\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>T</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mrow><msup><mrow><msup><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>−</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></msqrt></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Solve <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T prime of x, equals 0\"><math alttext=\"T prime of x, equals 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>′</mo></mrow></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></math></span></span> and find the values of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T prime of x\"><math alttext=\"T prime of x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>′</mo></mrow></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> changes sign from negative to positive. Evaluate <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T\"><math alttext=\"T\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></math></span></span> for those values of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to de